> DINOBOT turned over to CRYOTEK then, "That is for our current leader to
> decide.  IF the situation is as dire as you say, then you have wasted enough
> time alreayd, and must make an offer of proof then of what you have to give

<OLD>

There was a nod from CRYOTEK as DINOBOT looked at him.

"Yes." He said, there has been no real proof has there?" His question
was designed to needle her, to bring doubt upon her claims.

ANTAGONY's response was swift, "What? You think I would waste my time
playing tricks on you?" She seemed genuinely frustrated, and angry and
anxious.

She reached into a section of armor, which caused the TERRORCONS to
raise their weapons menacingly at ANTAGONY.

"Keep your armor on" The ebony colored ant said fiercely. "I just
wanted to show you something." ANTAGONY held out a locator device and
then threw it to CRYOTEK. "Go check it out for yourself."

CRYOTEK caught it smoothly and looked at it.

"It could be a trap." HUN-GRRR said as he glanced over at CRYOTEK.

He shook his head, "No, I believe her." CRYOTEK said easily. He looked
over at ANTAGONY, "I mean after all, she will remain right here with
us until we can be sure that she is telling us the truth."

ANTAGONY just grunted as she folded her arms over her chest.

CRYOTEK nodded, "Good." He said as he threw the device to DINOBOT,
"Get energized and go check it out." He turned to face  ANTAGONY,
"Take the Terrorcons with you."

Smiling CRYOTEK reached up for ANTAGONY's weapon, which she after a
moment of hesitation gave over.

"Meanwhile Antoagony and I will get much better acquainted." CRYOTEK's
smile got darker as he removed her weapons' charger pack and threw it
into a bin.

(TAG)

- Preston
